      "description": "Solid budget-friendly driver with honest cosmetic wear and the kind of mechanical simplicity that makes it a great project, commuter, or spare vehicle. Starts up, runs, and offers a usable platform for someone who appreciates straightforward engineering and easy wrenchability. Not a show car, but a practical rig with good parts value, everyday utility, and plenty of life left for the right owner. If you want inexpensive transportation with project potential, this is a compelling buy.",
